Announcements for Stilwell Middle School:
*We are planning for school to begin on Wednesday, August 12. With that being said, our Open House schedule will begin with the 5th Grade on August 3, from 4 to 6pm. Students will be able to pick up their class schedules and meet their teachers. 5th Graders at this time are the only students who will be allowed to meet their teachers. Masks are required and social distancing is encouraged.
*Tuesday, August 4 will be the 6th Grade Open House from 4-6pm. Students will only be allowed to pick up their schedules.
*Monday, August 10, will be the 7th Grade Open House
and the 8th Grade will have theirs on Tuesday, August 11, from 4-6pm. These students will also be picking up schedules only, without meeting their teachers.

post_text:
8th Grade Graduation info:
The eighth grade graduation will be Tuesday night, May 12, 2020, at 7 pm in the high school student parking lot. Students should begin arriving about 6:15 pm to be parked and remain in your vehicles.
This is a private ceremony for parents and students only. Friends and family members are encouraged to park along 2nd street in town to cheer for the graduates as they are led through town with a police and fire escort. This parade should begin about 7:15 pm.

Please be aware, the weather forecast calls for possible bad weather. Should we be under any severe warnings, the graduation could be moved to Wednesday night. If this situation arises, you will be notified by a phone cast.

Parents, all information for summer will be posted on our Facebook page and the school web page or you may call the school at 918-696-2685 extension 3221 with any questions.

post_text:
Ms. Hummingbird‚Äôs Lesson for the Day!

Spring Conversation Cards: Why is asking and answering questions important?
We ask questions in order to learn more about a topic and we answer questions to provide information. To answer questions, students think about the meaning of the question, form an answer and speak the answer they formed. To ask a question your child has to think about what they want to ask, form a question in their mind and then produce the question they want to ask.
Asking and answering is part of how we learn! It is important to form complete sentences that have meaning.

This activity targets: articulation, WH question (who, what, when, where and why), vocabulary and formation of sentences.

post_text:
Stilwell High School will join other high schools nationwide on Friday to honor the 2020 Senior Class!

High schools around Oklahoma and across the country are banding together to honor the 2020 senior class amidst the coronavirus pandemic.

On Friday, April 10, at 8:20 p.m., James Bradley Memorial Field and outdoor stadiums around the state and country will turn on their lights for 20 minutes to show their appreciation for the senior class as part of the ‚ÄúBe the Light‚Äù campaign.

The lights are a beacon to show the Senior Class we are thinking of them and to remind them there will be a time where we will be all together once again.

The ‚ÄúBe the Light‚Äù campaign has been spreading across the nation as schools look for a way to celebrate their graduating seniors who are having their final memories in high school stripped away due to the Covid-19 virus.

Take a drive by the field during that time and honk to show your support. Please remember to adhere to social distancing protocol and stay in your vehicle.

Why the exact time?
20:20 for 20 minutes for the Class of 2020!

post_text: Molecules in soap have hydrophilic and hydrophobic ends and when hydrophilic liquid food dye is suspended on top of the soap, in this case, shaving cream, it is suspended. If you put a piece of paper on top of this suspension the food dye is attracted to the hydrophilic cellulose, causing it to soak into the paper in whatever pattern you formed. Beautiful results! #preApScience ü§ì
text: Molecules in soap have hydrophilic and hydrophobic ends and when hydrophilic liquid food dye is suspended on top of the soap, in this case, shaving cream, it is suspended. If you put a piece of paper on top of this suspension the food dye is attracted to the hydrophilic cellulose, causing it to soak into the paper in whatever pattern you formed. Beautiful results! #preApScience ü§ì
